h we infer that\nthe higgsino mass parameter $\\mu$ can be measured to a precision of about\n$\\Delta\\mu=$2--7 GeV. For the electroweak gaugino mass parameters $M_1$, $M_2$,\nwhich are chosen in the multi-TeV range, a narrow region is compatible with the\nmeasurements. For both parameters independently, we can determine a lower\nbound.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 12 Jul 2013 20:11:50 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 10 Dec 2013 21:04:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-01-10"}
